entries.title: Meet Tom Emmer: lawyer, hockey player, father of seven and the new House majority whip
entries.description: The new House Majority Whip, Tom Emmer of Minnesota, is used to playing in barnburners as he takes the reins from now-House Majority Leader Steve Scalise, R-La.

entries.title: Dak Prescott scores 5 touchdowns as Cowboys wallop Bucs in NFC wild-card matchup
entries.description: Dak Prescott put on a show as the Dallas Cowboys blasted the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on the road to win their NFC wild-card matchup and advance to play the San Francisco 49ers.

entries.title: Tom Brady irks NFL fans with apparent slide-tackle attempt on Cowboys player
entries.description: Tom Brady on Monday night faced criticism for an apparent slide tackle on a Dallas Cowboys player during the Tampa Bay Buccaneers' playoff game.

entries.title: Carville claims media 'making fools of themselves' with 'both sides' coverage of Biden classified docs
entries.description: Democratic strategist James Carville criticized the mainstream media for overhyping the scandal surrounding President Biden keeping classified documents.

entries.title: TUCKER CARLSON: This is bigger than just a story about classified documents
entries.description: Fox News Tucker Carlson discusses the latest in the Biden classified documents scandal on 'Tucker Carlson Tonight.'

entries.title: Cowboys kicker makes unfortunate history after third missed extra-point attempt, Dak Prescott gets frustrated
entries.description: Dallas Cowboys kicker Brett Maher made dubious history with his three missed extra-point attempts against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.

entries.title: Exes Sean Penn, Robin Wright spotted together for first time in nearly 6 years
entries.description: Exes Sean Penn and Robin Wright were photographed in a rare public outing together at Los Angeles International Airport over the weekend. The couple divorced in 2010 and share two children.

entries.title: Florida shooting at Martin Luther King Jr. Day event leaves eight people wounded: reports
entries.description: Eight people were wounded in a shooting at a Martin Luther King Jr. Day event in Fort Pierce, Florida, on Monday evening, according to local news reports.

entries.title: John Larroquette was paid in marijuana to narrate 'Texas Chainsaw Massacre,' talks 'Night Court' reboot
entries.description: John Larroquette confirmed internet rumors and admitted he worked for free, but was paid in marijuana for voiceover work on the classic '70s horror film.

entries.title: Michigan woman, 2 kids died of hypothermia in field, sheriff says
entries.description: A Michigan woman and her two kids died of hypothermia while taking refuge in a field, according to news reports.

entries.title: New Mexico police arrest failed GOP state House candidate in shootings targeting Dem politicians' homes
entries.description: A failed GOP candidate for New Mexico's House was arrested Monday afternoon in connection with a string of shootings targeting Democratic politicians' homes.

entries.title: Ex-intel official who signed Hunter Biden laptop letter admits significant portion of emails 'had to be real'
entries.description: Douglas Wise, a former top intel official, admits most that was found in Hunter Biden's emails first reported by the New York Post "had to be real" when he co-signed the open letter.

entries.title: Tom Brady throws first red zone interception since 2019; Cowboys capitalize on turnover
entries.description: Tom Brady's attempt to throw the football away in the red zone was thwarted with an interception from Dallas Cowboys safety Jayron Kearse.

entries.title: Dallas teenager shoots 11-year-old bystanding boy during fight: police
entries.description: A juvenile girl in Dallas, Texas, fighting with another girl allegedly shot at her opponent, but the bullet struck an 11-year-old boy who was a bystander.

entries.title: Deion Sanders upset with roughing the passer penalty on Bucs: 'This is ridiculous'
entries.description: Deion Sanders was upset with a roughing the passer call on the Tampa Bay Buccaneers when Akiem Hicks hit Dallas Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott.

entries.title: 'Titanic' director James Cameron says 'new investigation' will 'settle' Jack and Rose 'door' debate
entries.description: James Cameron is putting the door-debacle of Jack and Rose behind his 1997 film "Titanic" to the test in an upcoming National Geographic documentary.

entries.title: Timeline of Biden classified documents has critics asking: What were they doing in those two months?
entries.description: 'The Five' co-hosts discuss the latest after three sets of classified documents were found at the Biden Penn center and President Biden's Delaware home.

entries.title: JUDGE JEANINE PIRRO: Patience is running thin with Biden on classified documents mess
entries.description: Fox News' Judge Jeanine Pirro reveals the more classified documents are found the more Democrats' patience runs thin and despite the White House's push back, the media continues to seek answers on 'Jesse Watters Primetime.'

entries.title: Tom Brady happy to have key offensive lineman back ahead of playoff game: 'It's a big boost for us'
entries.description: Tom Brady welcomed veteran center Ryan Jensen back to the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Monday ahead of the team's playoff game against the Dallas Cowboys.

entries.title: Arizona Republic editor recalls another time Biden mishandled classified documents: 'Someone screwed up'
entries.description: Arizona Republic published an article by executive editor Greg Burton Sunday in which he recalled witnessing then Vice President Biden mishandle classified documents.

entries.title: Boston police arrest man for 2007 murder of Massachusetts mother
entries.description: The Boston Police Department arrested a man on Saturday for allegedly murdering Felicia McGuyer, more than 15 years after the 32-year-old mother disappeared.

entries.title: Tom Brady wishes Rob Gronkowski would be on field with him; ex-NFL star jokes about passing physical
entries.description: Tom Brady was gearing up Monday to take on the Dallas Cowboys in the Tampa Bay Buccaneers' playoff game, but he wished he had one player with him.

entries.title: California Berkeley university campus worker finds human skeleton in unused residence building: police
entries.description: A human skeleton was discovered last week in an abandoned building near the main campus of the University of Berkeley, but police are unsure how long it was there.

entries.title: Lisa Marie Presley public memorial planned at Graceland
entries.description: Lisa Marie Presley's family arranged a public memorial service at Graceland in Memphis on Sunday, Jan. 22. The daughter of Elvis Presley died on Thursday at 54.

entries.title: Lamar Jackson shares cryptic message amid murky future with Ravens
entries.description: Lamar Jackson shared a cryptic message on his Instagram account on Monday after the Baltimore Ravens lost to the Cincinnati Bengals in the playoffs.

entries.title: Astrophysics 'steeped in systemic racism and White supremacy,' says Colorado College science professor
entries.description: A Colorado professor believes Astrophysics is steeped in systemic racism and white supremacy and wants to change how physics is being taught and foster an inclusive environment.

entries.title: Republicans respond after Biden calls them 'fiscally demented': 'absolutely zero self-awareness'
entries.description: Republicans fired back at President Biden after he called them "fiscally demented" while speaking at Al Sharpton's National Action Network Martin Luther King, Jr. Day event.

entries.title: Justice in the Senate? West Virginia governor 'very interested' in challenging Joe Manchin
entries.description: West Virginia Republican Governor James Justice II told Fox News he is seriously considering a Senate bid against Democratic incumbent Joe Manchin.
